{
 "name": "RPlog_Brig_-_Day_Two",
 "title": "Brig: Day Two",
 "summary": "Still chained in the detention block of the I2SD Inquisitor, the former Commodore Lynae Caiton and Antoine Dareus endure their second day of captivity. Captain of the Line Jal'Dana Rall, an old rival whose career Lynae once derailed, visits the cell to lecture Lynae about pride and betrayal and to coldly report that she personally executed one of Lynae's officers; when Lynae refuses to rise to the taunts, Jal'Dana strikes her, threatens Dareus at blasterpoint, and knees him before departing with a vow that someone like her will always come for Lynae. Later, Lynae's oldest friend Davyd Levvis, newly elevated in rank, arrives and quietly presses her to explain why she ran. Lynae lays out her reasoning, that arresting the CDU diplomat Kiare violated the treaty she held sacred and that she returned to prevent a needless war, before bitterly condemning the new Emperor for spitting on everything she and her fellow officers sacrificed. Unable to wash his hands of hunting traitors, Davyd turns to leave, pausing only to whisper that he had once loved her, leaving Lynae stunned.",
